-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Computacenter, Next Plc and Standard Life Plc
-- 
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 01:28AM EDT
-- None



March 17 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Computacenter, Next Plc and Standard Life Plc, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Computacenter <CCC.L>: Barclays starts with underweight; Jefferies raises price target * Next <NXT.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 7500p  * Valeo SA <VLOF.PA>: Barclays raises price target to 114 euros from 83 eurosFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Computacenter <CCC.L>: Barclays starts with underweight; price target 600p * Computacenter <CCC.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 720p from 470p; rating hold * Hellenic Carriers <HCLL.L>: Panmure raises target price to 60p from 50p; rating buy * Next Plc <NXT.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 7500p from 7000p; rating buy * Salamander Energy <SMDR.L>: Barclays cuts price target to 130p from 160p; equal weight * Standard Life Plc <SL.L>: Barclays raises price target to 377p from 349p; equal weight * Valeo SA <VLOF.PA>: Barclays raises price target to 114 euros from 83 euros; overweight